n
C_n=\{\cos(k \pi/n)\},
k=1, \ldots, n/2 -1
s_n
(a,b) \subset (0,1)
a,b \approx 1
|a-1|=|a-b|=O(1/n^2)
s_n=O(n)
s_n=O(n^2)
C_n \cap (a,b)
a
b
n
a_n=1-C/2n^2
b_n=1-C/4n^2+o(1/n^2)
C
k
\cos(k\pi/n)=1-k^2\pi^2/2n^2+o(1/n^2)
a_n\lt\cos(k\pi/n)\lt b_n
C/4\leqslant k^2\pi^2/2\leqslant C/2
\sqrt{C/2}/\pi\leqslant k\leqslant\sqrt{C}/\pi
C
s_n
n\to\infty
s_n=O(1)
s_n\to s_\infty(C)
C\to\infty
s_\infty(C)\sim\lambda\sqrt{C}
\lambda=(1-\sqrt2/2)/\pi
\lambda\approx0.09323
